Can you Outrun a Bad Diet?

I get number of queries, of people asking, so if I'm not really following a clean meal plan  can I cover it up with intense workouts?

You have heard this time and again, patience is the key. 
It's easier said that done. But I can give you multiple examples of what a little patience can do. 
( Check #fwptransformations )💯💯 

Sadly most of us falter too quickly and resort to crash diets, just to leave that Mid way too. So instead of making a new year resolution, that may or may not last (given previous experiences)💯 Go easy on yourself. Do things that you love, eat foods that make you happy with maintaining a balance of essential foods too. 

Well, this video will give you the answer..

12 years back on this day, I started my first venture.

I was scared, leaving a high paying job to start something that might workout or fail miserably, but never the less, we took that step. 

We had our set of downs, then even more and back then I understood, what “hitting the rock bottom actually meant” 

But one thing for sure. “SHEER HARD WORK”, I can vouch that talent takes you far, but hard work keeps you in the game .. There’s not even a single month since we started, that feels we haven’t hustled and that probably is the fuel that keeps me going, yet.

That one step, has led to meeting so many amazing folks, building a gorgeous team and everything around it .. 

But can’t conclude the post without thanking everyone who’s been a part of this journey and continue to do so..
Thank you and we ain’t stopping 💙🧿🔥

PS : Happy Birthday HiringMonk 
Daddy loves you 🫶🏻
